Examination:
Patient appears well, alert and oriented,
extraocular movements intact, face is symmetric at rest
with activation, symmetric UE movements.

Prior in-person neurological examination:
MOCA 27/30
General:
appears well, in no acute distress.
Eyes:
ophthalmoscopic exam reveals sharp optic discs and normal
retinal vasculature bilaterally.
Cardiovascular:
Well-perfused
Resp: Comfortable on RA
Abd:
Non-distended
Extremities: No rashes or lesions
appreciated

MS: alert and oriented x3, follows
commands, no aphasia, no dysarthria.
